## What is AbuSentry?

AbuSentry is a collection of scripts that can be used by security professionals or analysts to perform various security related tasks. Tasks that are performed by the scripts include, but are not limited to, vetting the status of a URL, extracting text from a URL, performing a urlscan analysis, and performing a virustotal analysis, and more.

## Installation

### Using PIP

The abusentry toolkit is available on [PyPI](https://pypi.python.org/pypi), see [https://pypi.python.org/pypi/abusentry](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/abusentry).

The easiest way to install it is using [pip](https://pip.readthedocs.org/en/latest/installing.html).

```bash
pip3 install abusentry
```

> **Note:**
> If an error occurs during the installation process, check your permissions. It might be required to run pip as root.

### From Scratch

It's also possible to install the library from it's source code. You will then be able to use the latest possible version or even try the [develop branch](https://github.com/xransum/abusentry/tree/dev).

The first step is to clone the repository of the project:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/xransum/abusentry.git
```

Then, you can install the library using the following command:

```bash
cd abusentry
python3 setup.py install
```

## Usage

### Command Line Interface

The abusentry toolkit comes with a command line interface (CLI) that allows you to use the tools from your terminal.

```bash
abusentry --help
```

But you can also use the tools directly from the command line:

abusentry interface:
```bash
abusentry --help
```

dnscheck script:
```bash
dnscheck --help
```

ipcheck script:
```bash
ipcheck --help
```

sniper script:
```bash
sniper --help
```

urlscan script:
```bash
urlscan --help
```

virustotal script:
```bash
virustotal --help
```

unshorten script:
```bash
unshorten --help
```

## Documentation

The documentation is available at the following address: [https://github.com/xransum/abusentry](https://github.com/xransum/abusentry).

It contains how to use the library and even how to contribute, plus it contains the technical documentation for the project.

